# Payments Domain – Stakeholders

# Purpose

This document identifies all stakeholders interacting with the Payments Domain, defines their responsibilities, and establishes communication and escalation mechanisms.

The goal is to ensure clear ownership, reduce ambiguity, and enable efficient collaboration between business and technical teams.

---

# Stakeholders Identification

The Payments Domain interacts with a diverse set of internal and external stakeholders.

## Internal Business Stakeholders

* Product Management
* Finance Team
* Accounting Team
* Customer Support Team
* Operations Team
* Compliance & Risk Team

## Internal Technical Stakeholders

* Backend Engineering Team
* Platform Engineering Team
* DevOps / SRE Team
* Data Engineering Team
* Security Engineering Team

## Cross-Domain Consumers

* Orders Domain
* Customer Domain
* Billing Domain
* Subscription Domain
* Notifications Domain
* Fraud Detection Systems
* Analytics & Reporting Platforms

## External Stakeholders

* Payment Service Providers (PSPs)
* Banking Institutions
* Regulatory Bodies (indirect)
* External Auditors (periodic)

---

# Roles & Responsibilities

## Product Management

* Define payment-related business requirements.
* Prioritize payment features and enhancements.
* Align payment capabilities with business strategy.

## Finance & Accounting

* Validate payment correctness and reconciliation outcomes.
* Define financial reporting requirements.
* Ensure compliance with accounting standards.

## Customer Support

* Investigate customer payment issues.
* Handle payment disputes and inquiries.
* Trigger operational workflows when needed.

## Backend Engineering

* Design and implement payment workflows.
* Maintain payment APIs and domain logic.
* Ensure correctness of payment state transitions.

## Platform Engineering

* Provide infrastructure for payment services.
* Maintain shared services (API gateway, messaging, etc.).
* Ensure scalability and reliability of payment systems.

## DevOps / SRE

* Monitor system health and performance.
* Manage deployments and incident response.
* Maintain SLAs and reliability targets.

## Security Engineering

* Define and enforce security standards.
* Monitor for vulnerabilities and threats.
* Ensure compliance with security policies.

## Data Engineering

* Provide payment data pipelines.
* Ensure data availability for analytics and reporting.
* Maintain data integrity across systems.

## External Providers (PSPs & Banks)

* Process payment transactions.
* Return payment status updates.
* Ensure settlement of funds.

---

# Communication Plan

Effective communication ensures alignment across all stakeholders.

## Operational Communication

* **Channel:** Incident management tools (e.g., PagerDuty, Opsgenie)
* **Purpose:** Real-time alerts, incidents, system degradation
* **Audience:** SRE, Engineering, On-call teams

## Business Communication

* **Channel:** Regular sync meetings, dashboards, reports
* **Purpose:** Payment performance, KPIs, feature updates
* **Audience:** Product, Finance, Operations

## Technical Communication

* **Channel:** Engineering channels (Slack, Teams), ADR reviews
* **Purpose:** Architecture changes, integration updates
* **Audience:** Engineering, Platform, Security

## Cross-Domain Communication

* **Channel:** API contracts, event schemas, documentation
* **Purpose:** Integration alignment between domains
* **Audience:** All consuming and producing domains

## External Communication

* **Channel:** Provider dashboards, support tickets, APIs
* **Purpose:** Payment processing issues, outages, reconciliation
* **Audience:** PSPs, banking partners

